<TITLE> Govt's job to cut prices: commerce minister </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 11 (bdnews24.com)  Commerce minister Muhammad Faruq Khan on Sunday said the prime job of the government, since it was elected with people's mandate, is to cut the prices of essentials. "We must work neutrally and in accordance with law and, as mandated by people, our prime job now is to reduce the prices of essentials, which is people's demand," the minister told his colleagues in the ministry. He sought cooperation, support and advice from the officers to achieve the goal, a commerce ministry official said in a press statement. Faruq outlined some guiding factors in his speech to the officials of the commerce ministry. He urged the officials to prove their skills by working selflessly and on mutual consultation, the statement added. Commerce secretary Firoz Ahmed, additional secretary Golam Mustakib, Export Promotion Bureau vice chairman M Hasabullah, Trading Corporation of Bangladesh chairman M Rizaul Islam, heads of different departments and ministry officials were present at that time
